/******************************************************************************

Create a Java# program that will ask the user to enter values for base and height 
of a right triangle. Thereafter, the program will display the correct area of 
the right triangle. Put the formula in a method called rightTriangle. The main 
method should only display the output. Copy the code from your IDE then paste 
the code in the text box provided. 

//Sample Input:

Enter base =               (assuming I will press 5 and press the enter key)
Enter height =           (assuming I will press 5 and press the enter key)

//Processing: DO NOT CHANGE THIS FORMULA  area = (base*height)/2

//Sample output:

The area of the right triangle = 12.5

*******************************************************************************/
import java.util.Scanner;
public class Main
{
	public static void rightTriangle(){
	    Scanner myScan = new Scanner(System.in);
	    float base, height, area;
	    
	    System.out.print("Input base: ");
	    base = myScan.nextFloat();
	    
	    System.out.println();
	    System.out.print("Input height: ");
	    height = myScan.nextFloat();
	    
	    area = (base * height)/2;
	    System.out.println();
	    System.out.println("The area of the right triangle = " + area);
	}
	
	public static void main(String[] args) {
	    
		rightTriangle();
	}
}


